{"type": "article", "id": 31731, "title": "它是个秤？不不，这是个可爱的错觉｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2016-09-01T23:09:58Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 32303, "name": "Studio Naama Hofman"}, {"id": 32304, "name": "NECKTIE studio"}, {"id": 7901, "name": "NakNak"}, {"id": 32305, "name": "The Big Tiny"}, {"id": 32306, "name": "Mark Laban"}, {"id": 32307, "name": "Mika Tolvanen"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 11, "praise_count": 101, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160901235109SbRMYaOrwCB8ygm5.jpg", "contents": "<p>          </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Tube Pendant Collection by Studio Naama Hofman</h3><p>提起枝形或者是其他款式的吊灯，你脑海中浮现的第一个造型是什么？如果你更青睐于能够轻松变换造型的吊灯，<a href=\"http://naamahofman.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Naama Hofman</a> 工作室以模块化为理念打造的 <a href=\"http://naamahofman.com/work/tube-pendant-collection/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tube</a> 系列或许会让你眼前一亮。卷轴似的圆柱形 LED 灯管穿插在黄铜管两端的圆环中，成为了这个纤细多变的结构中桥梁一般的存在，允许人们在组装时展现自己的创意。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235347Y5Na2r3QujkeDx8n.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.706667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235347Wt2A5kRznsvxaE8p.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.290000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609012353487OqH8og2CeJtKNDl.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.703333\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235348wR3mksITChz7cZxL.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.705000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235348W1CsMDceIRX8pPyk.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.772656\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609012353473oLw7pQ1UdqamPry.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.290000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Tiny Tower by The Big Tiny Co</h3><p>以不正确的姿势长时间使用笔记本电脑会对身体造成不小的负荷，澳大利亚公司 The Big Tiny 的联合创始人 Matt Cramsie 就饱受颈椎间盘突出的烦恼。当他发现市面上现有的抬升桌面无法同时兼容美观和便携性之后，他决定设计一款面面俱到的支架：<a href=\"http://tinytowerlaptopstand.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tiny Tower</a> 仅重 800 克，收起状态下 1.8 厘米的厚度可以连同鼠标和键盘一道放进专用的托特包内，携带起来非常省心。当它展开后可将笔记本电脑提升 25.8 厘米，只要是 11 到 15 寸的笔记本电脑都可以使用。你可以通过<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/thebigtinyco/the-laptop-stand-youve-been-waiting-for-the-tiny-t\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>参与众筹，包含托特包的早鸟价为 89 美元。</p><p><br></p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235412wNQcqFvhGlDWdEzL.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.713235\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235409H7ldYqSDFTAQPCuI.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.705882\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235411xy1JA7fpnHLQZVoG.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.386765\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235408Yjnvb6at2QKMF0dB.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.705882\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235409N6UrdoYWDSLZJI1T.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.705882\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Digital Daiku by Mark Laban</h3><p>Daiku（<a href=\"https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%A4%A7%E5%B7%A5\" rel=\"nofollow\">大工</a>）在日语中意为木匠，由于采用了现代化的数码制作工艺，设计师 <a href=\"http://www.marklaban.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mark Laban</a> 就将两个词结合起来为这套木制家具命名。当你仔细端详这些作品时，也很难忽视 Laban 对于日本传统美学的鉴戒：名为 <a href=\"http://www.marklaban.com/temple-bench\" rel=\"nofollow\">Temple</a> 的长椅造型简洁端正，有着如同传统寺庙的轮廓；长凳 <a href=\"http://www.marklaban.com/rustic-stool\" rel=\"nofollow\">Rustic</a> 则利用重复的图案挖凿，使得光滑和粗糙两种质地并存，具有一种独特的优雅感。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235309ntrf4JYCDeK3Z58X.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563570\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235309BUrixubIYECLK8hA.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609012353088OHhWC9EtDAzgfRP.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235308kKeuFoQBzXM9Jntb.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235308KFmV7rDvef3q28hY.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235308g3J1nlpjr2C8LAUs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.737164\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Wearable Shelter by Dr. Harriet Harriss et al.</h3><p>对颠沛流离的难民们来说，居所对他们的身心至关重要，然而制作帐篷所需要的时间以及成品有限的大小很难为这些远离家乡的人们提供必要的舒适。来自伦敦皇家艺术学院的 Harriet Harriss 教授<a href=\"http://www.reuters.com/article/us-design-wearables-syria-refugee-idUSKCN0VI18O\" rel=\"nofollow\">指导十位学生</a>为难民们设计了这件名为 Wearable Shelter 的大衣，只需要花上一分钟左右的时间就能转换成一个睡袋或者是帐篷。它由特卫强（Tyvek）制成，这种材料不仅光滑轻薄，还具有很强的抗拉和防水性。虽然这件大衣并不以提供长久居所为目的，但对不少到达欧洲后需要三周时间才能抵达难民安置中心的人来说，或许能带去一些帮助和温暖。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235236w4MKsE8FpV6iyCcu.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235236eu8IzlgNLwkJCFvT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235236oSmg30iELIG2tOlQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235237DopS3cIdne407PQX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Moment Scale by NECKTIE studio</h3><p>还记得白熊钓鱼的<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/29435.html\">陶瓷杯盖</a>吗？日本 <a href=\"http://necktie.tokyo/\" rel=\"nofollow\">NICKTIE</a> 工作室最近又推出了一件让人感到不可思议的设计，第一眼看到 Moment Scale 时，你觉得它是用来做什么的呢？是不是想试试放点什么上去？尽管看起来和普通的秤没什么区别，但它并不会根据你放在托盘上的物品改变指针的位置，能推动指针的只有来自时间的力量。这是它的<a href=\"http://necktie.onlinestores.jp/category/select/pid/8770\" rel=\"nofollow\">购买链接</a>，售价为 18000 日元。 </p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235206M7mbro2WTYAShZHK.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235205biZH4nKtWJ20TMeB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235205IsX4iQAaGzcjeT9o.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235205SkEngj5ywqOsi3Bx.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235206x2mMz0n8dgE1qTpH.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235205RXW3T2hrYtaA91Bq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.750000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Hoop umbrella stand by Mika Tolvanen</h3><p>这款名为 Hoop 的伞架由芬兰设计师 <a href=\"http://www.studiotolvanen.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mika Tolvanen</a> 为台湾品牌 <a href=\"http://www.naknakdesign.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">NakNak</a> 打造，由可以储水的铸铁底座和它上方的支架构成，不仅实用更体现出了一种极简的美感。它实际上是 Tolvanen 基于在跳蚤市场发现的一个老式铸铁支架设计的，虽然在外形上和那件 1950 年代的古董有了很大的区别，但延续了干净利落的结构。这是它的<a href=\"http://www.naknakdesign.com/product/item/25-HOOP\" rel=\"nofollow\">购买链接</a>，售价为 149 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235131zTI85ULc3l0KoaWh.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714844\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609012351319ltQRPSbenV62zad.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714844\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235131aVJQSFEiuO73GPAD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714844\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201609012351316izu0M5vQ7Rh4HcU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714844\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160901235131qVg7whu2szPy384r.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714844\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}